This paper deals with the problem of embedding and visualizing high-dimensional data in a two-dimensional space, which is a common problem in machine learning and computer vision. The paper proposes a novel method called PixelSNE, which is a highly-efficient, screen resolution-driven 2D embedding method with a linear computational complexity in terms of the number of data items. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories:

- cs.LG (Machine Learning): This sub-category deals with the development of algorithms and models for machine learning tasks, including dimensionality reduction and visualization.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): This sub-category deals with the development of algorithms and models for computer vision tasks, including image processing and analysis.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): This sub-category deals with the development of algorithms and models for various AI tasks, including machine learning and computer vision.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval): This sub-category deals with the development of algorithms and models for information retrieval tasks, including text and image search.
- cs.MM (Multimedia): This sub-category deals with the development of algorithms and models for multimedia tasks, including image and video processing and analysis.
